<P>

<s docid="LA121190-0089" num="50"> Photo, Space Review: A White House report recommended that NASA build an alternative launch vehicle to the space shuttle -- which it called expensive and risky -- and develop stringent limits on manned flights.</s>

<s docid="LA121190-0089" num="51"> At a news conference, above, NASA Administrator Richard Truly -- with Vice President Dan Quayle, who heads the National Space Council -- said his agency will seriously examine the suggestions.</s>

<s docid="LA121190-0089" num="52"> Agence France-Presse</s>
</P>
