<s docid="FBIS3-40520" num="90"> In the meantime, one of the main goals in developing the autonomous space robot is to perfect the busing work involved in capturing and releasing a target satellite.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-40520" num="91"> In order to develop a space robot that will be able to perform the required busing work on its own, one of the major things that must be done is to develop test apparatus that enable us to do simulations on the ground that take into account the bi-directional movement of the target satellite captured with the satellite vehicle in a zero-gravity environment so that we might develop the necessary control algorithms, busing sensors, and confirm these functions and operations.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-40520" num="92"> Therefore, Mitsubishi Electric has been working on a ground-based test apparatus called the ``busing simulator'' equipped with an arm that will enable the motion of the satellite vehicle and the target satellite to be simulated during capture and release of the target satellite by the arm.</s>

